		<td><b>Re: Why do video games on consoles need to be licensed?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Games on the Famicom didn't need to be licenced, as it had no lockout chip.<br /><br />In the US the atari market was crippled with extremely low quality games, which caused the great video games crash. Which is why Nintendo introduced the lockout chip and licensing for their NES. To be honnest, this was mostly a successful measure, although it didn't prevent shitty games to appear at least those could play correctly and be exept from obvious bugs such as crashing when selecting a level or things like that.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


